<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style=""><div style="margin: 0px;"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Last week we announced our partnership with the British Council. I have received some questions following the announcements and have set out below further information that I hope will address some of the questions people may have:</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Firstly, it is normal in NAE schools and other schools to network, collaborate and interact with the wider community which may include use of facilities. These type of arrangements all have a benefit for the school as whole, the children at school or the school employees. We also wish to grow our school and events and activities that bring people to our school will help increase awareness across Yangon.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Also, in common, and beyond our core education offers, our organisations strive to build capacity and skills in the wider community and set benchmarks for helping Myanmar become a more prosperous and inclusive society. You can read more how the British Council does this across Arts, Society, Education and English in the attached summary of its work in Myanmar.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">We have entered a partnership on a trial basis lasting one year. The partnership will continue to be reviewed during this time.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Our expectations of the partnership</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">As part of the partnership the British Council has agreed to support BSY by further enhancing our quality offer and our community by:</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Briefing our students &amp; parents on UK educational opportunities and helping them navigate the UK Further and Higher Education environment</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Providing specialist IELTS exam support for students intending to apply for prestigious schools, colleges and universities overseas</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Helping our local corporate services, security, and support staff with their English language to enable them to interact effectively with all our parents and students</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting parents who would like to enhance their English communication skills, or better support their children build skills in English in their primary years.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Helping students on pre entry to the school that may need extra English support.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Future partnership work on potential summer schools</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">· &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Working with us to support our students and parents to build a better understanding of the best of UK culture and education</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">In return for their support we have agreed that the British Council will run two classes at BSY in the evenings and four at the weekends. All classes will operate outside of our normal school hours, in rooms currently not being used by any of our students. The British Council will only have access to the empty rooms as designated and no other facilities.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">All staff and resources will be provided by the British Council and our teachers will not be involved in any way. We anticipate there being very little impact on the day to day running of the school and all of BSY’s child protection and security policies will be respected and enforced.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">BSY, as a private education school, and the British Council have very different educational offers, but as organisations we have similar values and expectations around quality education. As UK and multinational organisations we both follow world-leading quality standards in child protection, health and safety and security.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">I hope this helps clarify the situation. I will also be holding an information session on Thursday morning at 8.10am in the school theatre.</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Thank you</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Paul Holyome&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Principal&nbsp;</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><br></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" size="2">www.britishschoolyangon.org</font></p></div></div>]]></td>
